post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

post_text: A note from Taylor Libraries: All of your teachers and students qualify for a Taylor library card, because you work and/or go to school in Taylor. If anyone in your school family needs/wants access to free ebooks, eaudiobooks, streaming movies, music, and more, we can get everyone a temporary online library card within one business day. With library cards, all your kids can, for example, read the same ebooks together using Hoopla or watch the same documentary using Kanopy. Staff or parents go to our website and fill out a temporary library card request form online (linked on the front page). Our staff will email back with their login info and links to all the resources we have.

post_text: We had a fun visit from the Detroit Red Wings School Assembly Team. Coach Ryan and his team spoke to the students about determination, healthy eating and the importance of exercise. We had students participate in a stick handling relay, and a teacher vs. student shoot out!! The teachers won 2-1!! We got some equipment donated and all students are coming home with their own Red Wings folder with information for you and a Red Wing ticket fundraiser.

Every month the Quest staff select a member of our Quest staff family to be knighted Lord/Lady of Quest Academy. This month we celebrate Ms. Taha!
Ms. Taha is new to Quest this year in the role of office administrator. Since day one she has worked diligently to learn about the school and puts 110% effort into everything she does. She cares about our school, our families, and our scholars and has been a great addition to our team!
Congrats Lady Taha💙
